title: David.Hudson.Didgeralia.MP3@224kbps
description:
Didgeralia - David Hudson

This is a textured musical creation of percussion with the ageless Didgeridoo creating rhythms and tempos that will enrich and enlighten the listener. 



Artists:

* David Hudson       - Didgeridoo, Additional Percussion and Chants
* Giuseppe Vizzone   - Drums, Percussion



01. Trekking - Walkabout with a purpose. When one would walk long distances
    escaping climate change.
02. Warrama - Aboriginal corroborree.
03. Conversation - Part One
04. Roundup - Stockmen mustering cattle. Aboriginal men were often stockmen on
    cattle stations.
05. Wungal
06. Territorial Fight - Eagle defending it's hunting rights.
07. Conversation - Part Two
08. Djembe
09. New Shoes - Feeling good, walking proud.
10. Gidja The Moon - Legend that is reflective and mystical.
11. Taipan - This suggests the movement of a snake, namely the venomous taipan.
